  "root_text": {
    "sn56.14:0.1": "Saṁyutta Nikāya 56.14 ",
    "sn56.14:0.2": "2. Dhammacakkappavattanavagga ",
    "sn56.14:0.3": "Ajjhattikāyatanasutta ",
    "sn56.14:1.1": "“Cattārimāni, bhikkhave, ariyasaccāni. ",
    "sn56.14:1.2": "Katamāni cattāri? ",
    "sn56.14:1.3": "Dukkhaṁ ariyasaccaṁ, dukkhasamudayaṁ ariyasaccaṁ, dukkhanirodhaṁ ariyasaccaṁ, dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā ariyasaccaṁ. ",
    "sn56.14:2.1": "Katamañca, bhikkhave, dukkhaṁ ariyasaccaṁ? ",
    "sn56.14:2.2": "‘Cha ajjhattikāni āyatanānī’tissa vacanīyaṁ. ",
    "sn56.14:2.3": "Katamāni cha? ",
    "sn56.14:2.4": "Cakkhāyatanaṁ …pe… manāyatanaṁ—",
    "sn56.14:2.5": "idaṁ vuccati, bhikkhave, dukkhaṁ ariyasaccaṁ. ",
    "sn56.14:3.1": "Katamañca, bhikkhave, dukkhasamudayaṁ ariyasaccaṁ? ",
    "sn56.14:3.2": "Yāyaṁ taṇhā ponobbhavikā nandirāgasahagatā tatratatrābhinandinī, seyyathidaṁ—kāmataṇhā, bhavataṇhā, vibhavataṇhā—",
    "sn56.14:3.3": "idaṁ vuccati, bhikkhave, dukkhasamudayaṁ ariyasaccaṁ. ",
    "sn56.14:4.1": "Katamañca, bhikkhave, dukkhanirodhaṁ ariyasaccaṁ? ",
    "sn56.14:4.2": "Yo tassāyeva taṇhāya asesavirāganirodho cāgo paṭinissaggo mutti anālayo—",
    "sn56.14:4.3": "idaṁ vuccati, bhikkhave, dukkhanirodhaṁ ariyasaccaṁ. ",
    "sn56.14:5.1": "Katamañca, bhikkhave, dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā ariyasaccaṁ? ",
    "sn56.14:5.2": "Ayameva ariyo aṭṭhaṅgiko maggo, seyyathidaṁ—",
    "sn56.14:5.3": "sammādiṭṭhi …pe… sammāsamādhi—",
    "sn56.14:5.4": "idaṁ vuccati, bhikkhave, dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā ariyasaccaṁ. ",
    "sn56.14:5.5": "Imāni kho, bhikkhave, cattāri ariyasaccāni. ",
    "sn56.14:6.1": "Tasmātiha, bhikkhave, ‘idaṁ dukkhan’ti yogo karaṇīyo …pe… ‘ayaṁ dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti yogo karaṇīyo”ti. ",
    "sn56.14:6.2": "Catutthaṁ. "
  },
  "translation_text": {
    "sn56.14:0.1": "Linked Discourses 56.14 ",
    "sn56.14:0.2": "2. Rolling Forth the Wheel of Dhamma ",
    "sn56.14:0.3": "Interior Sense Fields ",
    "sn56.14:1.1": "“Mendicants, there are these four noble truths. ",
    "sn56.14:1.2": "What four? ",
    "sn56.14:1.3": "The noble truths of suffering, the origin of suffering, the cessation of suffering, and the practice that leads to the cessation of suffering. ",
    "sn56.14:2.1": "And what is the noble truth of suffering? ",
    "sn56.14:2.2": "You should say: ‘The six interior sense fields’. ",
    "sn56.14:2.3": "What six? ",
    "sn56.14:2.4": "The sense fields of the eye, ear, nose, tongue, body, and mind. ",
    "sn56.14:2.5": "This is called the noble truth of suffering. …” ",
